==English==
===Etymology===
{{confix|en|xeno|mania}}.  The components are of Ancient Greek origin.  When used in the context of Greece, the word is likely borrowed from modern {{m+|el|ξενομανία}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|en|eɪniə|s=5}}
===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
# A strong or excessive preference for foreigners or for foreign customs, manners, or institutions.
